#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.matmul:59
msgid "The behavior depends on the arguments in the following way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.matmul:61
msgid ""
"If both arguments are 2-D they are multiplied like conventional matrices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.matmul:63
msgid ""
"If either argument is N-D, N > 2, it is treated as a stack of matrices "
"residing in the last two indexes and broadcast accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.matmul:65
msgid ""
"If the first argument is 1-D, it is promoted to a matrix by prepending a 1 "
"to its dimensions. After matrix multiplication the prepended 1 is removed. "
"(For stacks of vectors, use ``vecmat``.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.matmul:68
msgid ""
"If the second argument is 1-D, it is promoted to a matrix by appending a 1 "
"to its dimensions. After matrix multiplication the appended 1 is removed. "
"(For stacks of vectors, use ``matvec``.)"
msgstr ""

